  "body": "<!-- Please use this template while reporting a bug and provide as much info as possible. Not doing so may result in your bug not being addressed in a timely manner. Thanks!\r\n\r\nIf the matter is security related, please disclose it privately via https://kubernetes.io/security/\r\n-->\r\n\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nFollowup on https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/74493#discussion_r260028479: Without a valid ConstructVolumeSpec(), UnmountDevice() is not called during reconstruction, so the global block mount will leak.\r\n\r\nAlso need to check if raw block local PV supports reconstruction.  There are no reconstruction e2es for raw block (https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/issues/74545), so maybe this needs to be verified manually for now unless we can quickly adapt the existing tests.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nWe may have to store metadata in a local file to support reconstruction, similar to what [csi does](https://sourcegraph.com/github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/-/blob/pkg/volume/csi/csi_plugin.go#L362)\r\n",
